### Configuration Summary

{%- set timeout_seconds = warehouse_statement_timeout | regex_replace('[^0-9].*', '') | int %}

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| **Multi-Cluster** | Enabled (1-3 clusters) |
| **Initially Suspended** | Yes (no cost until use) |
| **Auto-Resume** | Enabled |
| **Statement Timeout** | {{ timeout_seconds }} seconds ({{ (timeout_seconds / 60) | int }} minutes) |
| **Owner** | `{{ data_product_name | upper }}_ADMIN` |

### Tags Applied

Each warehouse will be tagged with:

| Tag | Value |
|-----|-------|
| `DOMAIN` | {{ data_product_domain | upper }} |
| `ENVIRONMENT` | {{ data_product_environment | upper }} |
| `DATAPRODUCT` | {{ data_product_name | upper }} |
| `WORKLOAD` | (varies per warehouse) |

**Note:** Tags enable cost allocation by domain, environment, and data product for all compute usage.